rComments: One of the best Professors that I have had. His lectures are interesting and fun. He is down to earth and is approachable when you have questions.

This professor is very knowledgeable and gives interesting lectures. As long as you do your work, and put effort into it he'll give you a good grade. Very accessible outside of class, and understanding
Rob is one of best Profs I have ever had. He is very understanding and will provide make up assignments when needed. I would definitely take another one of his classes.

Rob was an awesome prof. I had a couple of questions about the exam and he was quick to to get back to me. He's definitely funny and a bit sarcastic, but it made the course more entertaining. He's a very knowledgeable, down to earth and understanding guy, I would take one of his courses again.

One of the nicest and most understanding professors I have ever had and a very easy grader IMO - but the most disorganized man I have ever met. Did not respond to any of my several emails, no TA, and did not post the lecture material until days before the exam period. I would take him again just because it's so easy to get a good grade.

Nice guy but super boring as a lecturer. Terrible visual and audio quality for his device. Quite disorganized PPTs with a lot of long paragraphs he chants. Likes using hip-hop as examples but that's nightmare for someone who's not interested in that. Exams are easy as long as you're ok with his too-broad instruction.

This professor, though casual and kind, is something special... Incredibly disorganized. He did not post most of the class notes until two days before exam period, and did not tell us when the exam is until 6 days before. WILL NOT ANSWER URGENT EMAILS! I left him 12 wondering about the notes and the exam! Would not take this class again!

Rob is a great, casual guy. He is clearly very knowledgeable about world religions. Often uses personal anecdotes for entertainment and better understanding. Very understanding of lateness and lack of participation (especially in the morning). Open to letting you write about your interests as long as you clear it with him first, and a fair marker.

This professor is incredibly disorganized, it is ridiculous. I understand we are in a pandemic, but he seems to be my only professor out of everyone I had over the summer and this term that is THIS unorganized. Stay away if you like structure. If you're okay with things being done last minute and no clear communication, this is your prof.
